WorldStage Newsonline– Nigerian Breweries Plc, a leading brewing company in Nigeria on Thursday conformed share dealing by insiders involving its Foreign core investor , Heineken Brouwerijen B.V that purchased 72,500 units N36.00 per unit  which amounted to N2,610,000 while Ojakovo Joy Onoeme, the General Manager, Progress Trust CPFA Limited (A Nigerian Breweries Plc Subsidiary) also purchased 3,000 units at N34.50 per unit which amounted to N103,500 In a notification signed by Uaboi G. Agbebaku, Company Secretary released by the Nigerian Stock Exchange, Heineken Brouwerijen B.V transaction took place on 14th & 18th August, 2020 while that of Ojakovo Joy Onoeme took place on 13th August, 2020. Nigerian Breweries Plc, is the pioneer and largest brewing company in Nigeria. It serves the Nigerian market and exports to other parts of West Africa. No movement of the stock price of NB at N35 on Thursday on the Nigerian Stock Exchange as at Noon despite 15 transaction involving 36,252 share valued at N1,284,837.80. Nigerian Breweries Plc, is the pioneer and largest brewing company in Nigeria. It serves the Nigerian market and exports to other parts of West Africa. WorldStage earlier reported that Heineken Brouwerijen B.V   between 11th -13th August, 2020 purchased 274,542 units at N35.76 per unit (average) which amounted to N9,817,621.92 and Chief Kolawole Babalola Jamodu, a Non-Executive Chairman on 13th August, 2020 purchased 10,000 shares at N37.00 which amounted to N370,000